10.2 Deactivation of cookies/withdrawal of consent
You may withdraw your consent at any time without affecting the permissibility of the processing until this withdrawal. The easiest way to withdraw your consent is through our  Consent Manager
[LINK].
[LINK].
You can also control the use of cookies yourself, as most browsers have the option of limiting or completely preventing their storage. However, we would like to remind you that you will not be able to use all the functions of the website to their full extent in that case.
You can also opt out of the use of cookies for reach measurement and marketing purposes by visiting the Network Advertising Initiative opt-out page (
http://optout.networkadvertising.org/
), the US website listed here (
http://www.aboutads.info/choices
) or the European website (
http://www.youronlinechoices.com/uk/your-ad-choices/
).
10.3 Google Analytics
We use Google Analytics, a web tracking service provided by Google Ireland Limited, Gordon House, Barrow Street, Dublin 4, Ireland (“Google”). We use this tool so that we can analyse your user interactions on websites and in apps; we then use the statistics and reports obtained to improve our offering and to make it more interesting for you as a user.
Cookies,
Pages visited
Contents of orders placed
Achievement of website goals such as contact enquiries or newsletter registrations
User behaviour (e.g. time spent on a page, clicks, scrolling behaviour)
Approximate location (country, city)
Data on the device/browser, screen resolution, etc,
IP addresses and website or app activities. Your IP addresses are also recorded in Google Analytics to ensure the security of the service and to provide us as the website operator with information about the country, region or location from which the respective user originates (so-called "IP location determination"). For your protection, however, we naturally use the anonymization function ("IP masking"), i.e. Google truncates the IP addresses by the last octet within the EU/EEA.
Personal data such as name, address or contact details are not forwarded to Google Analytics. The data listed above may be transferred to servers in the USA. Google acts as a processor in this respect and we have concluded a corresponding contract with Google. Google is certified in accordance with the new Privacy Framework between the USA and the European Union and therefore guarantees an appropriate level of protection for your data.
Google Analytics stores cookies in your web browser for a period of 12 months since your last visit. These cookies contain a specially generated user ID that can be used to recognise you as a user on future visits.
The processed data is stored together with the user ID, which enables a pseudonymized evaluation of user profiles. This user-related data is automatically deleted after 14 months. Other, non-user-related data may be stored for longer.
If you do not agree to this processing, you can deactivate data collection by Google Analytics by installing a one-time browser add-on. Only necessary cookies are activated in our user-friendly default settings. Users can activate additional cookies separately.
The legal basis for the collection and further processing of the information (which takes place for a maximum of 14 months) is your consent (Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR) and Art. 6 FADP. You may withdraw your consent at any time without affecting the permissibility of the processing until this withdrawal. In apps, you can reset the advertising ID within the Android or iOS settings. The easiest way to revoke your consent is via our Consent Manager
[LINK].
[LINK].
[LINK].
or by installing Google’s browser add-on, which can be accessed at the following link:
tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout?hl=en/
.
More information on the scope of services provided by Google Analytics can be found at
marketingplatform.google.com/about/analytics/terms/us/
. Google provides information on data processing when using Google Analytics at
support.google.com/analytics/answer/6004245?hl=en/
.
General information on data processing, which according to Google also applies to Google Analytics, can be found in Google’s privacy policy at
policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en-gb/
.
10.4 Facebook pixel, Custom Audiences and Facebook Website Conversion
We use the Facebook pixel, which is provided by the social network Facebook, on the basis of your consent pursuant to Art. 6 (1)(a) GDPR. The Facebook pixel enables Facebook to recognise the visitors to our website as a target group to which to display advertisements (“Facebook ads”). In this way, we use the Facebook pixel to display Facebook ads placed by us only to those Facebook users who have also shown an interest in our website or who display certain characteristics (e.g. interests in certain topics or products determined on the basis of the websites visited), which we transmit to Facebook (“Custom Audiences”). The Facebook pixel also enables us to ensure that our Facebook ads correspond to the potential interest of the users and do not have a harassing effect. Furthermore, the Facebook pixel enables us to track the effectiveness of Facebook ads for statistical and market research purposes by seeing whether users were redirected to our website
    after clicking on a Facebook ad (“conversion”). The processing of the data by Facebook takes place within the framework of Facebook’s data use policy:
https://www.facebook.com/policy.php
. In order to maintain a high level of data protection, Facebook uses the standard contractual clauses of the European Commission.
More information can be found here:
https://www.facebook.com/business/help/651294705016616
You can amend the Facebook Custom Audiences function when logged in to Facebook by going to
https://www.facebook.com/settings/?tab=ads#
.
Likewise, you can manage your advertisement settings on Facebook when logged in to Facebook by going to
https://www.facebook.com/help/109378269482053/?helpref=hc_fnav
.
You can deactivate Google Analytics via the following link:
https://www.facebook.com/settings?tab=ads
.
10.5 TikTok Pixel
We use the TikTok Pixel, which is provided by the social network TikTok, which is operated by TikTok Technology Limited, 10 Earlsfort Terrace, Dublin, D02 T380, Ireland, on the basis of your consent pursuant to Art. 6(1)(a) GDPR.
The TikTok Pixel enables TikTok to recognise you as a visitor to our website as a target group to which to display advertisements (“TikTok Ads”). We use the TikTok Pixel to display TikTok Ads placed by us only to those TikTok users who have also shown an interest in our website or who display certain characteristics (e.g. interests in certain topics or products determined on the basis of the websites visited), which we transmit to TikTok (“custom audiences”). Furthermore, the TikTok Pixel enables us to track the effectiveness of TikTok Ads for statistical and market research purposes by seeing whether users were redirected to our website after clicking on a TikTok Ad (“conversion”).
In this context, we have also activated the Automatic Advanced Matching feature. This feature of the TikTok Pixel allows data such as hashed email address, name, gender, city, federal state, postcode and date of birth or phone number to be sent to TikTok as additional information, if you have provided us with this data. Using this feature enables us to tailor advertising campaigns on TikTok even more precisely to people who are interested in our products.
More information can be found at
https://ads.tiktok.com/marketing_api/docs?rid=5ipocbxyw8v&id=1701890972946433
.
More information about TikTok’s privacy policy can be found at the following link:
https://www.tiktok.com/legal/privacy-policy-eea?lang=en
.
10.6 Use of Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, Twitter, Pinterest and Snapchat plug-ins
Plug-ins from Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, Twitter, Pinterest and Snapchat (hereinafter referred to as “social media platform”) are used on our websites. You can recognise the plug-ins by their respective company logos. If you use one of these plug-ins, a connection is established to the server of the corresponding social media platform and your post is displayed on this social media platform. The social media platform thereby receives your IP address and which of our web pages you visited and when. If you are logged in as a member of a social media platform at the same time, the social media platform will assign this information to your personal user account. The social media service is able to determine your user name and even your real name based on the transmitted data and associate the information with your personal user account with the social media service. You can prevent this by logging out of your user account of the social media platform before using the plug-in. More information on the collection and use of data by Facebook, Instagram, YouTube, Twitter, Pinterest and Snapchat in relation to your rights and options for protecting your privacy can be found in the corresponding data protection notices of the social media platform.
11. Payment methods
Purpose and scope of data processing
As part of order processing in our online shop, we offer our customers various secure payment options. In addition to banks and credit institutions, we also accept payments made using other service providers (hereinafter collectively referred to as “payment service providers”).
When executing payments, the payment service providers process data such as names, addresses, payment and bank information (e.g. account and credit card numbers, passwords, TANs and check digits) and data relating to the contract, amount and recipient. All of this data is required to complete the transaction. However, we would like to point out that the data entered is processed exclusively by the payment service provider. We do not receive any bank account or credit card information; only payment confirmation or a notice of rejection. If necessary, the payment service provider will transmit the data to credit agencies for the purpose of checking identity and creditworthiness. For further details and information, please refer to the general terms and conditions and data protection notices of the relevant payment service provider.
With regard to payment transactions, the terms and conditions and data protection notices of the respective payment service provider apply and can be accessed on the corresponding websites or payment applications. The same applies to further information and to the assertion of the right of withdrawal, right of access or other rights of the data subject.
Payment services used:
Byjuno
– payment processing; service provider: Byjuno AG, Industriestrasse 13c, 6300 Zug, Switzerland; website:
https://www.byjuno.ch/
Privacy policy:
https://www.byjuno.ch/de/dataprotection
.
PayPal
– payment services and solutions; service provider: PayPal (Europe) S.à.r.l. et Cie, S.C.A., 22–24 Boulevard Royal, 2449 Luxembourg, Luxembourg; website:
https://www.paypal.com
Privacy policy:
https://www.paypal.com/uk/webapps/mpp/ua/privacy-full
.
12. Facebook and Instagram fan pages
Tally Weijl uses the technical platform and services of Facebook Ireland Ltd, 4 Grand Canal Square, Grand Canal Harbour, Dublin 2, Ireland and Instagram Inc., 1601 Willow Road, Menlo Park, CA, 94025, USA for the information service offered by these platforms and services.
We would like to point out that you are responsible for your own use of these pages and their functions. This applies in particular to the use of the interactive functions (e.g. commenting, sharing, rating). Alternatively, you can also access the information provided on these pages at any time via our website at
www.tally-weijl.com
.
When you visit our Facebook or Instagram pages, they collect data that includes your IP address and other information that is present on your PC in the form of cookies. This information is used to provide us, as the operator of the fan pages, with statistical information on the use of the Facebook and/or Instagram page(s).
More information about Facebook’s policy in this regard can be found at the following link:
https://www.facebook.com/help/pages/insights
And for Instagram can be found at: https://www.facebook.com/help/instagram/788388387972460
The data collected about you in this context is processed by Facebook Ltd and Instagram Inc. and may be transferred to countries outside the European Union. The data that Facebook and Instagram receive and how they use it is set out in general terms by Facebook in its data use policy. There you will also find information on how to contact Facebook and on the settings options for advertisements. The data use policy is available at the following link:
https://facebook.com/about/privacy
Facebook’s full data use policy can be found here:
https://facebook.com/full_data_use_policy
For Instagram, further information can be found at the following link: https://help.instagram.com/519522125107875
The way in which Facebook and Instagram use the data from the visit to Facebook and Instagram pages for their own purposes, to what extent activities on the Facebook page are assigned to individual users, how long Facebook and Instagram store this data and whether data from a visit to Facebook and Instagram pages is passed on to third parties is not conclusively and clearly stated by Facebook or Instagram and is not known to us.
When you access a Facebook or Instagram page, the IP address assigned to your end device is transmitted to Facebook. According to information from Facebook and Instagram, this IP address is anonymised (for “German” IP addresses). Facebook and Instagram also store data about the end devices of its users (e.g. as part of the “login notification” function); where applicable, this enables Facebook and Instagram to assign IP addresses to individual users.
If you are currently logged in to Facebook or Instagram as a user, there is a cookie with your Facebook or Instagram ID on your end device. This enables Facebook and Instagram to track that you have visited this page and how you have used it. This also applies to all other Facebook or Instagram pages. Using Facebook or Instagram buttons embedded in websites, it is possible for the companies to record your visits to these website pages and assign them to your Facebook and/or Instagram profile(s). This data can be used to offer content or advertising that is tailored to you.
If you want to avoid this, you should log out of Facebook and/or Instagram or deactivate the function that keeps you logged in, delete the cookies present on your device and close and restart your browser. This deletes Facebook and/or Instagram data through which you can be directly identified. This allows you to use our Facebook and/or Instagram page(s) without being identified. When you access interactive features of the site (Like, Comment, Share, Message, etc.), a Facebook or Instagram login screen will appear. If you log in, you will again be identifiable by Facebook and/or Instagram as a specific user.
Information on how to manage or delete data about you can be found on the following Facebook and Instagram support pages:
https://facebook.com/about/privacy#
https://help.instagram.com/196883487377501/?helpref=hc_fnav
The current version of the relevant privacy policy can be found at the link on the corresponding Facebook and Instagram page.
